Prestory meeting notes feedback from @<6E668580-F8AB-64C3-A4C1-1DDE45503DA2> :&nbsp;
FYI, @<4C46EFE8-26F9-6F48-B257-971123DDB984> , @<D2E79038-97CA-6D63-8A21-A92E9A844981> , @<DED1F3BE-FA1D-6B76-B3AE-F3AE291DCC5F> 

Prestory Mtg:

*   Provide user with text * &quot;If any communities are marked here, and the flag Restrict Users by Assigned Communities is on, the user will only see data for these communities. If no communities are associated, the user can see ALL communities for their organization(s)&quot;.... all the time, BUT if the flag is OFF, in another row, under that text, in YELLOW (Bootstrap &quot;Warning&quot;), also add &quot;Warning! The feature flag Restrict Users to Assigned Communities is OFF. You can assign communities but it will not affect the application.&quot;

**_I think this is ok for now. I am also flexible if you have a better way to portray it._**&nbsp;

*   Edge Case not in AC: If a builder has no communities, and the assigned communities link is clicked, the dialog opens and shows &quot;This builder has no communities to assign.&quot; Additionally, if the user is also a Sys-Admin, the message in the AC pertaining to that case is also shown. Simple list format; NO BULLETS.

**_Sounds good also_**&nbsp;

*   **Edge Case not in AC:**What happens if a user has assigned communities for a given buider and then their legacy role for that builder is changed to Sys-Admin? What should happen?..... 

    Assigned communities for the user and org. are retained, but VDS should disregard them for Sys-Admin users. **Question: Should we tell the user this in VEO Admi**_**n, when this change is made? If so, how?**_

**_For this story, I don't think we need to warn a user in VEO Admin when a user is being role-promoted from sales for example to something like sys-admin**. If we provided a warning, then it should just be that their powers in the app are being greatly increased overall and did you really mean to do this? **Regarding the assigned communities, I suppose I am ok with leaving them, I am also ok with wiping them out since a sys-admin should not have them_**&nbsp;  **Decision: Leaving them for now.**

The UI should handle current max length (DB) for builder name and legacy role name, without truncation. Longer names in the future will be dealt with at that time.

**_I guess here by &quot;handle&quot; you mean display?_&nbsp;Correct**

Layout of rows....columns for builder name, assigned communities, and legacy role should govern spacing on the row. Adust widths to accomodate specific fields as needed.

**_Ok, seems good_**&nbsp;

Rows for assigned communities in the dialog willl mimic the same selection interactions as the parent builderList component (color coding for pending addition/removal, undo buttons, etc.)

**_Ok, seems good_**
